  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do you drop off a U-Haul at a different location?",
  "response": "Dropping off a U-Haul at a different location is typically called a \"one-way rental.\" Here's a step-by-step guide on how you can manage this process:\n\n1. **Reservation**: When you initially reserve your U-Haul, specify that you intend to drop it off at a different location. This is important and will influence availability and pricing.\n\n2. **Pick-Up**: Pick up your U-Haul at the original location and ensure that you have all the necessary paperwork, including the rental contract, insurance information, and the address of the drop-off location.\n\n3. **Travel**: Use the U-Haul to complete your move or transport and head towards the designated drop-off location.\n\n4. **Drop-Off**:\n    - **Check Hours**: Make sure you know the operating hours of the drop-off location.\n    - **Inspect the Truck**: Prior to dropping the truck off, clean it, fill up the gas tank (usually you must return it with the same level of fuel as when you picked it up), and inspect it for any damages.\n    - **Mileage Check**: Ensure the mileage is accurately noted since additional mileage may incur extra charges.\n\n5. **Finalize Drop-Off**:\n    - Go inside the drop-off location and inform the staff that you are returning a one-way rental.\n    - Provide them with the rental contract and keys.\n    - Sign any necessary paperwork and verify that your rental has been appropriately closed out. Keep copies of any documents.\n    - If you drop off the U-Haul after hours, use the designated key drop-off box and follow any instructions provided to complete the return process. Often, you'll need to log in to your U-Haul account and finalize the return online.\n\n6. **Confirmation**: Ensure you receive confirmation that the vehicle was returned successfully and that no additional charges are pending.\n\nBy following these steps, you can ensure a smooth drop-off process at a different location.",
